{"TopicId":215861,"ForumId":139,"TopicTitle":"Between Two Patches","CreatedByName":"Nate Simpson","CreatedById":205123,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:35:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nate Simpson","CreatedById":205123,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:35:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.png.18a4d5a231d74996db5cfdb5d7a37d99.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022640\u0022 data-ratio=\u002221.00\u0022 data-unique=\u0022fnv1li39l\u0022 style=\u0022width: 600px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.thumb.png.bb725c4c5ad8b49d3586052d455763c8.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile it\u2019ll be tough to beat the sheer number of fixes that went into \u003Cb\u003EPatch One\u003C/b\u003E, we\u2019re seeing quite a few big ones go down in \u003Cb\u003EPatch Two\u003C/b\u003E. We are still pulling a couple of late-breaking improvements into that build - once we\u2019ve got it in QA\u2019s hands we should be able to give you a date, and of course full patch notes will be posted when the build goes public. Until that time, here are a few things that are already checked into Patch Two:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed loss of vehicle on reference frame change when physicsless parts present\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed flamed-out engines not restarting properly\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEnabled switching between vehicles in atmospheric flight (within PhysX bubble)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRecovered Kerbals now return to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E Kerbal Manager\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nGave click priority to planets rather than moons when zoomed out in Map view\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nStruts and fuel lines no longer broken after cloning subassembly in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed bug: vessels with no control deleted during save\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed flowers on Kerbin\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded \u0022next\u0022 button to seizure warning screen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nHeight fog added to all atmospheres\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUpdated parking garage collision (now possible to enter structures)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nVarious CPU and GPU optimizations to improve performance\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are other improvements that we\u2019re hoping to squeeze into Patch Two (one of which got checked in last night), so hopefully a few more big-ticket items will get added to the list in the coming days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere are a couple of screenshots to show our progress. We have pruned all the hovering flowers made of squares and replaced them with flowers made of flowers:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022637\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.png.10d22b0552d6f19bdbbf41fa6e010472.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022637\u0022 data-ratio=\u002238.42\u0022 data-unique=\u0022g8j3h669v\u0022 style=\u0022width: 700px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.thumb.png.c19b732c738b746070a675fdf370d8ab.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u2019re also pretty excited about how nice the new height fog is looking. It\u2019s a subtle change, but it adds a lot of depth to the landscape:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022638\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.png.1ded27c89becf1e88ea40a384e3f94b8.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022638\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.33\u0022 data-unique=\u0022wb75mfeex\u0022 style=\u0022width: 700px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.thumb.png.a0cb9d2fafbc921977f43ab839270c1e.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn other news, I did a Discord AMA this morning, and you can read \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reddit.com/r/KerbalSpaceProgram/comments/120smy0/324_ama_with_nate_answers/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esome speedily-typed transcriptions of my answers here\u003C/a\u003E (thanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225122-dakota/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225122\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225122-dakota/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dakota\u003C/a\u003E). Thank you for all your questions - we received literally thousands of them and did our best to include as wide a variety as possible. This was lots of fun, and we\u2019ll be doing more AMAs in the future! We\u2019ll do our best to choose different questions the next time around so that things don\u2019t get too repetitive. If you\u2019ve got thoughts about how we can improve our AMA process, please let us know!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u2019ve also got another \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/215801-community-highlights-2/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ECommunity Highlights post on the forum\u003C/a\u003E - it\u2019s very exciting to see how Patch One has unblocked some more ambitious missions! Please keep sharing your creations in the #ksp2_screenshots\u00A0and #ksp2_challenges Discord channels- our team is fueled by your \u003Cs\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Ecrashes\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/s\u003E achievements! We\u2019ve also added an upvote system to both of those Discord channels. If you like something, add an :upvote: emoji. If an image in one of those channels gets fifteen or more upvotes, it\u2019ll appear in a new channel called #ksp2_bestof. If you posted a screenshot you\u2019re proud of that has now been lost in the mists of time, feel free to resubmit your creation so that the community can give it the upvotes it deserves!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the KSP Forums have themes now! You can opt into them by clicking the theme dropdown at the bottom of the page:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022639\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.png.e66598be6d0277430a92567bde513956.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022639\u0022 data-ratio=\u002218.00\u0022 data-unique=\u0022urzzq0o51\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.thumb.png.6464177abfb7560821cfe943158f5e3a.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd speaking of Weekly Challenges, we\u2019ve got a new one: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/215787-weekly-challenge-5-land-on-duna/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethis week, we\u2019re heading out to Duna!\u003C/a\u003E Check out \u003Ca href=\u0022https://discord.gg/InterceptGames\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethe Discord\u003C/a\u003E for details!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave a great weekend. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 loading=\u0022lazy\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerballlistic07","CreatedById":225447,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:41:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTwo things:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679693700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the KSP Forums have themes now! You can opt into them by clicking the theme dropdown at the bottom of the page:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022639\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.png.e66598be6d0277430a92567bde513956.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022639\u0022 data-ratio=\u002218.00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.thumb.png.6464177abfb7560821cfe943158f5e3a.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne, didn\u0027t know I needed this!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679693700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVarious CPU and GPU optimizations to improve performance\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTwo, will the system requirements change at all? Even a smidge? (Please say yes I\u0027m begging)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for your continued work KSP team!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-24T21:41:59Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2023 09:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Kerballlistic07\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Datau03","CreatedById":223270,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:41:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks Nate and everyone else on the team! Have a nice weekend!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DibzNr","CreatedById":212219,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:42:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad we\u0027ve finally killed off Kerbin\u0027s outbreak of square flowers, can\u0027t wait for this update!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:43:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679694093\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerballlistic07\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Kerballlistic07 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne, didn\u0027t know I needed this!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy work will save thousands of eyeballs from lightmode!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:44:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlowers are made of flowers? You learn something new every day\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceExplorerW","CreatedById":217286,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:45:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks Nate and the team for the update ! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Clayel","CreatedById":223206,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:49:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679693700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the KSP Forums have themes now! You can opt into them by clicking the theme dropdown at the bottom of the page:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022639\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.png.e66598be6d0277430a92567bde513956.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022639\u0022 data-ratio=\u002218.00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_03/image.thumb.png.6464177abfb7560821cfe943158f5e3a.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese are new? I just noticed these a few days ago after scrolling down to the bottom of the page and thought they were always there. Nice to see development on an old forum page!\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe dark mode especially is very welcoming.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-24T21:50:07Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2023 09:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Clayel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T21:57:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265088\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679694581\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223206\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Clayel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Clayel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese are new? I just noticed these a few days ago after scrolling down to the bottom of the page and thought they were always there. Nice to see development on an old forum page!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027ve actually been enabled for a couple of weeks, they\u0027re just hidden at the bottom of the page! I was fixing up a couple things before wanting to share it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EvelynThe Dragon","CreatedById":227182,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:02:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen will we get re-entry effects? I was sorely disappointed in them not being there.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd honestly, the part selection is grim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:04:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery nice, addressing some \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003Ebig \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003Esmall pain points overall.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EDark mode is also especially welcome! Idk why light mode is the standard default mode.... \u003Cem\u003Edisgraceful\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EIf you can share this with us, would be curious to know if we can expect fixes for either the drag bugs, or asparagus bug in the next patch?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:06:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat job intercept! Can\u2019t wait\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-24T22:06:54Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2023 10:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Little 908\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:09:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679695455\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226996\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FlazeTheDragon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, FlazeTheDragon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDark mode is also especially welcome! Idk why light mode is the standard default mode.... \u003Cem\u003Edisgraceful\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was told by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003Eand \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/64714-gargamel/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002264714\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/64714-gargamel/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gargamel\u003C/a\u003Ethat there would be riots if I changed the default. I\u0027m more of a darkmode person myself, but totally respect getting attached to the way the forum has looked for \u003Cem\u003Echecks watch\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ea long time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr.Seno","CreatedById":224523,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:11:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope them adding height fog into the game this early would mean that the Devs are confident with the game Optimization\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/1437623226_rocket_1f680(3).png\u0022 title=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/1437623226_rocket_1f680(3).png\u0022 title=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/1437623226_rocket_1f680(3).png\u0022 title=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:14:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679695740\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225122\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dakota\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Dakota said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was told by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003Eand \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/64714-gargamel/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002264714\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/64714-gargamel/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gargamel\u003C/a\u003Ethat there would be riots if I changed the default. I\u0027m more of a darkmode person myself, but totally respect getting attached to the way the forum has looked for \u003Cem\u003Echecks watch\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ea long time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould probably just \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eset\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003Ethere specific themes\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/em\u003Eto light mode and, in secret, change default to dark mode. They would never know\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EosusUb.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u002296\u0022 width=\u002296\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/EosusUb.gif\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-24T22:14:38Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2023 10:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by FlazeTheDragon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MagnumBot","CreatedById":228212,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:15:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just wanna say, I specifically made an account to post about this, but I have kept faith with you guys this whole time and while I believe right now the game is in a rough spot (much better after patch 1) I cannot stress how important it is to community morale that you take the time our of your day to post things like this a couple times a month. I think that as long as you can keep communication open like this and continue to back it up then it will not take very long for the community\u0027s opinion to turn around for the better. I don\u0027t know fully what happened behind the scenes, I\u0027m guessing it can\u0027t be talked about because you\u0027re all so passionate about the game and it probably hurt you just as much to have to release it in a undone state as much as it did for people who were waiting so long to receive it this way. The main thing is that I and many others believe in you guys and this game, but in order to get everyone on board and keep morale up on the community end these posts will be crucial, thank you for all the work you put in,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngodspeed devs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sspeter78","CreatedById":228215,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:24:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265093\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679695360\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227182\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EvelynThe Dragon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, EvelynThe Dragon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen will we get re-entry effects? I was sorely disappointed in them not being there.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd honestly, the part selection is grim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes! Re-entry effects! Need this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:43:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265109\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679696642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228215\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sspeter78\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Sspeter78 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes! Re-entry effects! Need this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in patch two, later on, possibly patch 3/4\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T22:49:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeat. I\u0027m hoping y\u0027all can sneak in some terrain fixes at some point so I can resume driving Kerbin, but it\u0027s nice to see the flowers fixed lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jinkguns","CreatedById":125866,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T23:07:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan we please get the option to resize UI text? The UI is really hard to read on high resolution ultra wide screen monitors.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso can we add the ability to use the mouse wheel to change the POV height in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NoMrBond","CreatedById":69263,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T23:28:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679693700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed loss of vehicle on reference frame change when physicsless parts present\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes this also address the inability to stage launch from bodies?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was kinda distressing when challenged to an Apollo style mission, but if you tried to do the ascent stage launch from the Munar surface it would just... not let you leave, and keep teleporting you back to the ground because you were \u0022Landed\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cpt Kerbalkrunch","CreatedById":175588,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T23:39:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679693700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded \u0022next\u0022 button to seizure warning screen\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-24T23:42:27Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2023 11:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Cpt Kerbalkrunch\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EA fine example of listening to the community.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T23:43:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679693700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s a subtle change,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s way more than subtle change and I bet that was what everyone including my dog (which I don\u0027t have) and neighbor (who doesn\u0027t play KSP) wanted and needed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThings about to get even more pretty and today I was already blown away by volcanos on Ike and Dunian sunset.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-24T23:45:09Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2023 11:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Aziz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HammerTyme","CreatedById":227259,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T23:44:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u201CEnabled\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eswitching between vehicles in atmospheric fligh\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003Et\u201C\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003Eheck yes!!! Can\u2019t wait to replicate some SpaceX Falcon 9 launches and be able to switch to the booster and land it. Then switch back to the 2nd stage. \u00A0 Thank you!!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"woeller","CreatedById":174556,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T23:52:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679694234\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225122\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dakota\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Dakota said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy work will save thousands of eyeballs from lightmode!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorryyyy! Dark Reader was faster than you, it already fixed the internet. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:grin:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/grin.png\u0022 title=\u0022:grin:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}